name: Key 0000

attributes.Notes: Rumours says it once opened every door in Tibia.

notes:
It used to open every door in Tibia. However, that is not the case anymore. Shapeshifter was the owner of this key and many other unique keys. Since Shapeshifter was hacked, his key collection (including key 0000) was lost. Other collectors have tracked down the hacker and bought the key collection to preserve its history and did so successfully. The key eventually appeared on Optional PvP worlds in the hands of other collectors.
This key was added into the game by one of the map creators (before CipSoft became a big company they used volunteers to do areas). This person added the key into the game in secret. When CipSoft found out that there was a hidden key, they removed its function.
The old master key was wooden (brown) and the new one is magical (purple).

Karr's old house with Shapeshifter's keyPast Test serverOld master keyWooden Key 0000 on Pacera in 2023

Go down to a room with three Cyclops and down again to a small cave with some Rats. The corpse is located in the south-east corner under some rubbish. This key opens the door to a room, over the Minotaur Outcasts' camp, where Cyclops guard Key 3610 and some other treasures. There's a Lever that allows access to the same room by moving part of the wall but it also closes the way back and can only be used once every Floor Reset.
Key 3610 is needed for the Devil Helmet Quest which is a level 30 quest but you need to get past level 40 Gate of Expertise to get key 3667.

notes: Opens the door to the Desert Dungeon Library. You need Key 4022 to get this key.here

name: Key 4022

attributes.Origin: You can get this key from Hagor. Hints are found in this book.
attributes.Notes: You need to give a Roll to Hagor to get this key and it allows access to the room containing Key 4009, which opens the Desert Dungeon Library.

notes: It opens the door to the small room where Key 4009 is. You can get it giving a Roll to Hagor.
buyfrom: Hagor in Jakundaf Desert sells for 1Roll

name: Key 4023

attributes.Origin: One can get this key from Adrenius. Some hints are found in the Desert Dungeon Library.
attributes.Notes: You can get this key when you take Adrenius' quiz and 500 gold piece.

notes: Opens the door to the Desert Dungeon Teleport Room. You will receive this key when you take Adrenius' quiz for 500 gold pieces

name: Key 4033

attributes.Notes: May be used in the Desert Dungeon.

notes: Apparently used in the Portal Hall. This key may not exist.

name: Key 4037

attributes.Origin: You can get this key in a quest by helping the blind NPC, Nemal. Hints are found in the Desert Dungeon Library.
attributes.Notes: You need help a blind NPC to get this key. You need bring to Nemal a Roll, a Rose, Flour, a Lump of Dough, and, a Cherry. Find it and tell him: blind, potion of regained vision, yes, yes, 31, and finally, nalus murtu.

notes: Opens the door to the Hall of Lost Doors. To receive a key from Nemal you must have all ingredients listed in the recipe, Roll, Rose, Flour, Lump of Dough, Cherry.

name: Key 4055

attributes.Origin: Hidden in a hollow stone south of the Desert Dungeon entrance.
attributes.Notes: Access to the Panpipe Quest.

notes: Allows you to open the door (here) to the Panpipe Quest.

name: Key 4210

attributes.Notes: Old guild hall key. This key is no longer in use.

notes: Most likely a Red Rose or Mercenary Tower Guildhall key in Fibula. This key is no longer in use.

name: Key 4501

attributes.Origin: In a treasure chest protected by a Minotaur Guard and a few Minotaurs in a cave below the Ice Islands.
attributes.Notes: Used to enter/exit Alawar's Vault storage room.

notes: This key is used for opening a room with three minotaurs below the Senja Castle.

name: Key 4502

attributes.Also Known As: Senja Castle Key, Alawar's Vault Key
attributes.Origin: In a treasure chest protected by a Minotaur Mage and a few Minotaurs in a cave below the Ice Islands.
attributes.Notes: Used to enter/exit Alawar's Vault.

notes: This key is used for entering and exiting Alawar's Vault (below Senja Castle).

name: Key 4503

attributes.Also Known As: Folda Restricted Area Key, Minotaur Archer Dungeon Key
attributes.Origin: In a treasure chest under the Ice Islands.
attributes.Notes: Used to open the door to the Restricted Area of Folda dungeon.

notes: This key provides access to the Protected Area under the Ice Islands.

name: Key 4600

attributes.Origin: Unobtainable now. Previously, bought from Seymour for 5 gold.
attributes.Notes: Training Room in the Rookgaard Academy. This key is no longer in use.

notes: Provided access to the Training Rooms in Rookgaard Academy. This was changed with the revamp of Rookgaard and the introduction of The Rookie Guard Quest. This key is no longer in use.

name: Key 4601

attributes.Origin: Can be found in a Chest near the Bear Room after revealing a hole with a Pick located here.
attributes.Notes: Key to Bear Room. It is found in a chest near the Bear Room, to the southeast, in a pick hole.

notes: This key is found here and allows you to enter the Bear Room, site of the Bear Room Quest, on Rookgaard. The room contains some valuable items. You will need a Pick to obtain this key.

name: Key 4602

attributes.Origin: No one knows or they are not telling.
attributes.Notes: May not exist. May be the key of the Minotaur Mage room.

notes: This key may not exist. Supposedly it opens the Minotaur Mage room. Many players say they have it, but is very unlikely.

name: Key 4603

attributes.Origin: Can be found at end of the "Corpse Alley" inside one of the bodies.
attributes.Notes: Katana Quest Room in Rookgaard.

notes: Used in the Katana Quest. This key allows you to enter the room before the Katana Room.

name: Key 4900

attributes.Notes: Thais Troll Cave single room key.

notes:
It used to open a door in a single room of Thais Troll Caves, here. It is unknown if copies of this key still exist. Furthermore, any existing copy might not be functional anymore, since many old keys are said to have been disabled with the Summer Update 2007. 
It's also not known for sure what material it was made of, however, it's assumed to be Silver since most other Thais keys were made of this material.

name: Key 5000

attributes.Origin: Hidden in a stone coffin under Wyda's house.
attributes.Notes: Wyda's house.

notes: Allows you to open the door to the room in Wyda's house.

name: Key 5002

attributes.Notes: Used to open a door in the Black Knight's Villa. This key is no longer in use.

notes: Used to open a door with no exit in the Black Knight's Villa. Some players in Antica and Pacera have this key. This key is no longer in use.

name: Key 5010

attributes.Origin: It can be found in two different dead trees, both west of the Black Knight's Village in Venore.
attributes.Notes: Opens door to the Black Knight's Villa.

notes: This key provides access to the caves beneath the Black Knight's Villa in Green Claw Swamp.

name: Key 5050

attributes.Origin: Found in a box in Dark Cathedral, in the room west of Angelina's room.
attributes.Notes: Angelina's cell in Dark Cathedral.

attributes.Notes: Pits of Inferno maze key.

notes: This key was part of the first draft of The Pits of Inferno Quest, but it was not obtainable in game anymore when the quest was released to players. Passing the door is not necessary to go through the maze, but it can still be opened by pulling one of the levers in there.

name: Key 6010

attributes.Origin: Reward from the Parchment Room Quest.
attributes.Notes: Reward from the Parchment Room Quest and used to Demon Helmet Quest access

notes: Opens the door to the Demon Hell, below the Hero Cave.

name: Bronze Prison Key
notes: Low chance to obtain it from an Unrealized Dream. Allows access to Zavarash's chamber for 1 person. Use it at the Roshamuul Prison when standing on the respective tile to be teleported to him.

name: Chayenne's Magical Key
notes:
Was a very rare loot from Chayenne's Anniversary Remains during Tibia's 15th Anniversary. In August 2012, CipSoft also held the Chayenne's Farewell Contest in which had this item as a reward to three winners. It's a valuable item because of its exclusiveness and because a quest requires it. As a consequence of its rarity, the quest's exclusive reward is also very valuable.

Required to be within the players inventory to enter the Realm of Dreams during the Realm of Dreams Quest.

name: Copper Prison Key
notes: Low chance to obtain it from an Unrealized Dream. Allows access to Horadron for 1 player. To use it, go to Roshamuul Prison and use it while standing on the respective platform.

name: Eye Key
notes: Part of The Secret Library Quest.

name: Forged Glowing Key
notes: It is quite hot; better not touch it with your bare hands.Part of the Hidden Threats Quest.

name: Forged Key
notes: You have restored this key to its original state.Part of the Hidden Threats Quest.

name: Golden Prison Key
notes: Chance to obtain it when using an Unrealized Dream. Allows access to Prince Drazzak's chamber for you and 4 team members; to use it, go to the Roshamuul Prison.

name: Intermediate State
notes: It doesn't feel quite finished.Part of the Hidden Threats Quest.

name: Key of Numerous Locks
notes:
Since TibiaCz left the fansite programme, this item cannot be obtained anymore.Mastrik from Refugia has a key of numerous locks.You can only read the text if you stand 2 SQMs from it or closer.
Its replica is the Key of Numerous Locks (Replica).

name: Key of Numerous Locks (Replica)
notes: You can obtain this item by trading 20 Silver Raid Tokens to Jorge. This item is a replica of Key of Numerous Locks.
buyfrom: Jorge in Adventurers' Guild sells for 20Silver Raid Tokens

name: Key to Knowledge

attributes.Classification: Plants, Animal Products, Food and DrinkCreature Products

notes: This is one of the two items required for the Forbidden Knowledge achievement.  If you have already eaten a  Forbidden Fruit, then upon using the  Key to Knowledge on the  Forbidden Tome, both of which will be consumed, you will receive the following message along with the Forbidden Knowledge achievement: You gained a tremendous amount of knowledge.

name: Key to the Drowned Library

attributes.Classification: Plants, Animal Products, Food and DrinkCreature ProductsQuest Items

notes:
Unlock bookcases in the Drowned Library, of Fiehonja. See also: Key to the Drowned Library/Statistics  

At least three of these are needed during Liquid Black Quest. You must use it on Seashell Bookcases to randomly obtain Seashell Books.

name: Lotus Key
notes: It is part of the Secret Library Quest. It is found on a skeleton in the Asura's Mirror, and, it is used to open the door where the Key of the Eye is found.

name: Magical Cage Key
notes: Even though the interaction with the barrel you get it from suggests otherwise, every player with access to Eclesius' cellar can get this key daily.Found in The Scatterbrained Sorcerer Quest.

name: Old Silver Key
notes: Part of the Forgotten Knowledge Quest.

name: Omrabas' Bone Key
notes: Looks the same as a Bone Key and a Goblin Bone Key.Obtained and used during The Gravedigger of Drefia Quest.

name: Omrabas' Copper Key
notes: Looks the same as a Copper Key.Obtained and used during The Gravedigger of Drefia Quest.

name: Prison Cell Key
notes:
Looks the same as a Crystal Key.
Item temporarily obtained in The Hidden City of Beregar Quest.
keywords: the hidden city of beregar quest
quest: The Hidden City of Beregar Quest

name: Silver Prison Key
notes: Low chance to obtain it from an Unrealized Dream. Allows access to Terofar's chamber. Use it on in the Roshamuul Prison when standing on the respective platform to be taken to him.

name: Strangely Ornamented Key
notes: Find it in the Haunted Tomb. You have a chance to get it by using the sarcophagus in the tomb. But be careful because every time you touch a sarcophagus you will lose life points. You will need two of these to enter The Dream Courts Quest room.

name: Theodore Loveless' Key
notes: Looks the same as a Silver Key, and, it is obtained momentarily from NPC Chantalle for mission 6 of The Thieves Guild Quest.

name: Tin Key
notes: It looks like a normal key, but it can only be found by hunting War Golem's, and, it is needed to tame a Tin Lizzard . It has a small chance of breaking when used and has a very rare chance that the key will not break but the lizard will.
